    <h3 class="font-weight-bold">1: Avion</h3>
    <img src="https://j.gifs.com/L9EXxp.gif" style="float:right; height:500px; width:650px" />
    <p style=" text-align:left">Avion has everything going for him that I like about this game. He's got a really cool area to fight in that's a flooded 
        castle looking place. The path leading to him is very foreboading as you head to the center of this inclosed space with fog all around you. You'll see him there
        as he's sleeping in front of you perched on a pole. Then to get on him is the coolest thing where you have to jump on him as he dives to get 
        you and then once you're on him that fanstastic music begins to play as you have to traverse this big bird mid flight to take him down.</p>
    
    <hr /><hr /><hr /><hr /><hr /><hr /><hr /><hr /><hr /><hr /><hr /><hr /><hr /><hr /><hr /><hr /><hr /><hr />

    <img src="https://media.giphy.com/media/3o6EQaAxwqYByiZXIQ/giphy.gif" style="float: left; height: 500px; width: 650px" />
    <h3 class="font-weight-bold" ; style="text-align:right">2: Gaius</h3>
    <p style=" text-align:right">Gaius also has such a cool area to fight in and its this raised platform in the middle of the lake.
        This platform actually helps you take him down becasue you need to get him to smack his sword into a metel plate into the middle of the
        platform. This will break his armor and then to get on him you can climb his sword to get at his weak points. Gaius also has a really cool design 
        where he sort of looks like a robot. The music of course is awesome but he can be a little finiky with getting his A.I. to actually swing his sword at the plate 
        so he's coming on in at number 2. </p>

    <hr /><hr /><hr /><hr /><hr /><hr /><hr /><hr /><hr /><hr /><hr /><hr /><hr /><hr /><hr /><hr />
    
